org.apache.plc4x.edgent

Class PlcFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.plc4x.edgent.PlcFunctions

  • public class PlcFunctions
extends Object
    WIP - A plc4x Apache Edgent Supplier and Consumer connector factory.

    TODO: Are there cases where a single logical poll would want to read from multiple addrs/data (of different types) from a device and bundle the values into a single TStream tuple (e.g., a JsonObject)? How would we support that? Is there a similar need for writing to multiple addrs/values on a device? Ah... NOTE: plc4c "batch" requests are coming and will help to address this.

    Sample use to read plc device data into an Edgent TStream: 

    
 PlcConnection plcConnection = new PlcDriverManager().getConnection("s7://192.168.0.1/0/0");
 plcConnection.connect();
 PlcConnectionAdapter adapter = new PlcConnectionAdapter(plcConnection));

 DirectProvider dp = new DirectProvider();
 Topology top = dp.newTopology();
 TStream<Byte> stream = top.poll(PlcFunctions.byteSupplier(adapter, "INPUTS/0", 1, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
 stream.print();
 dp.submit(top);

    Sample use to write Edgent TStream data to a plc device: 

    
 PlcConnection plcConnection = new PlcDriverManager().getConnection("s7://192.168.0.1/0/0");
 plcConnection.connect();
 PlcConnectionAdapter adapter = new PlcConnectionAdapter(plcConnection);

 DirectProvider dp = new DirectProvider();
 Topology top = dp.newTopology();

 TStream<Byte> stream = ...
 stream.print();
 TSink<Byte> sink = stream.sink(PlcFunctions.byteConsumer(adapter, "OUTPUTS/0"));

 dp.submit(top);

      • booleanConsumer

        public static org.apache.edgent.function.Consumer<com.google.gson.JsonObject> booleanConsumer(PlcConnectionAdapter adapter,
                                                                                              org.apache.edgent.function.Function<com.google.gson.JsonObject,String> addressFn,
                                                                                              org.apache.edgent.function.Function<com.google.gson.JsonObject,Boolean> valueFn)
        Create a new Edgent Consumer to write data to the plc device.

        TODO: Is it premature to supply this?

        Every call to the returned Consumer.accept(Object)

        • calls addressFn to get the device address string
        • calls valueFn to get the T to write
        • writes the value to the device address using the connection associated with the PlcConnectionAdapter.
        Parameters:
        adapter - the @{link PlcConnectionAdapter}
        addressFn - Function the returns a device PlcField from a JsonObject
        valueFn - Function the returns a Value from a JsonObject
        Returns:
        the Consumer<JsonObject>

        // TODO: No need to import the Topology module for just this comment ... I think //see org.apache.edgent.topology.TStream#sink(Consumer)
